# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics@^1.6.1` using npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with resolved dependencies

### 2. Root Layout Configuration (src/app/layout.tsx)
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, placed after the `</Providers>` closing tag
- The Analytics component will now track page views and user interactions across the entire application

## Implementation Details

The project uses the App Router architecture (Next.js 13+) with a `src/app/` directory structure. The Analytics component was added to the root layout at `src/app/layout.tsx`, which ensures it will be present on all pages of the application.

### Code Structure
The Analytics component is positioned correctly within the body tag:
```tsx
<body>
  <Providers>
    {children}
    <Toaster />
  </Providers>
  <Analytics />
</body>
```

This placement ensures analytics tracking is initialized for all pages while maintaining the existing component hierarchy.

## Verification

### Build Status
- The Next.js build process was executed
- TypeScript compilation completed successfully
- Note: There is a pre-existing build error related to a missing Resend API key in `/api/reserve` route, which is unrelated to the Analytics implementation

### Linting
- ESLint was executed successfully
- No new linting errors or warnings were introduced by the Analytics implementation
- Existing warnings in the codebase are unrelated to this change

### Package Management
- Used npm (the project's package manager) as indicated by `package-lock.json`
- Lock file properly updated with new dependencies

## Files Modified
1. `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
2. `package-lock.json` - Updated with resolved dependencies
3. `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component

## Next Steps
Once this PR is merged and deployed to Vercel, the Web Analytics will automatically start collecting data. No additional configuration is required, though you can view analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab for your project.
